fields.title: A frequent go-to
fields.body: I don't usually eat cup noodles but these are an exception. I buy them in big packs at costco and they're perfect for a light lunch. The kimchi flavor really comes through.

fields.title: One of the originals but not that great
fields.body: I used to eat these frequently but I have found other ramen to be a lot less bland. I still pick up a cup occasionally at the grocery store though.

fields.title: Not a fan of kimchi but these are decent
fields.body: I got these when they were out of all the other flavors. Usually don't like kimchi but these are acceptable which is saying something.

fields.title: Easy, quick, and tasty
fields.body: This is really good. Easy as well. Good for lunches at work if all you have access to is a microwave. Very quick and so tasty!! Not to be used with boiling water. You can...but I donâ€™t think it would work out as well.

fields.title: Nice Flavor!
fields.body:
I like my food spicy, and this ramen does just the trick when I'm cold and looking for something toasty! It's super affordable like all other ramen, but I like mixing mine with cheese and vegetables so that it doesn't taste the same as all the other ramen! It's definitely one of my favorite comfort foods!

fields.title: Chili Flavor
fields.body: When you just don't have time to cook or all out on grocery, what left is ramen noodles. Perfect for snowy day and when it's spicy! ðŸ˜‹

fields.title: Wow!
fields.body: i am a huge fan of ramen noodles and of the Nongshim brand 'ramyun' noodle. However, I took a shot in the dark with this Black line. The soup is a great soup, it tastes very similar to the Nongshim Gourmet Spicy ramyun. However, it's a tad bit less spicy.

fields.title: These are Seriously DELICIOUS Noodles!
fields.body: I added in some beef that I stir fried with onions, carrots, and Chinese cabbage. After mixing in the stir fried beef with vegetables, I got the dish pictured top right. It was AWESOME! This tasted just like a savory lo mein dish.

fields.title: Delicious
fields.body: What I love about them is that you can put anything into them, salmon, broccoli, asparagus etc. and with no muss end up with a great lunch or dinner item.

fields.title: I hate admitting it
fields.body: I hate admitting it, but this ramen is my greatest guilty pleasure. I really like spicy stuff so I also add sriracha.
